data.name: label25.Text
data.value: Just like the unsaved logs, app errors are another kind of log that stores exceptions that occur in the code. App errors are saved locally (in this app's root folder) in JSON format. The path format is "...\ERRORS\year\month\day.json" (eg. "...\ERRORS\2023\01\17.json"). This helps the developer to debug and fix bugs.

data.name: label17.Text
data.value: Unsaved logs... why? Logs are important. Especially when it comes to automations that can control numerous other services. So every raised/fired event, gets logged along with all the actions (a.k.a. IFTTT applets) that it has. Logs are saved locally (in this app's folder) in JSON format. The path format is "...\LOGS\year\month\day.json" (eg. "...\LOGS\2023\08\26.json"). Therefore, the "unsaved logs" section is a mechanism that helps to keep in the current session of the app, all the logs that could NOT be saved to file due to any error. This helps with debugging or understanding why some events are not processing correctly.
